<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="2687d967-9221-43af-932c-78f3547cf928" >

    <p>For two-stage alarms, please listen carefully to distinguish the signal, as there will be two different tones.</p> 
<p>For the first stage, the signal is a slow, intermittent tone, and it signifies a “be alert” signal. In this case, stand by and be alert for potential evacuation of the building. Listen to any announcements made.</p> 
<p>For the second stage, a fast, continuous tone signifies an “alarm” signal, and you must evacuate the building immediately. Do not wait for further announcements. Do not use the elevator.</p> 
<h3><strong>Stage 1: Warning signal to stay alert</strong></h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>You will hear a voice announcement providing information and instructions, and a bell signal that is intermittent (every five seconds).</li> 
 <li>Action: Stay where you are, get ready to leave, and await further instructions.</li> 
 <li>If the alarm stops, then all is clear and you may resume regular activities.</li> 
</ul> 
<h3><strong>Stage 2: Evacuation signal to leave the building</strong></h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>You will hear a voice announcement providing information and instructions, and a bell signal that is steady and continuous.</li> 
 <li>Action: Proceed to the closest, safest exit and move away from the building.</li> 
 <li>Security and fire wardens will confirm when re-entry to the building is allowed.</li> 
</ul> 
<h2>Questions?</h2> 
<p><strong>For questions regarding building evacuations or drills</strong>, please contact the <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1jRYdLYBDffv5xS3WV16ePwSaeP1JHsN65OFhNrFcQgU/edit#gid=1777590508"><span class="sr-only">google sheet</span>fire warden<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-file-excel-o"></span><span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a> in your area or Environmental Health and Safety at <a href="mailto:ehs@ryerson.ca">ehs@ryerson.ca</a> or 416-979-5000, ext. 553770.</p>
    





</div>
